[normal]On Thursday 26 December, 
[normal]we
[normal] received a further email with an apology – 
[normal]cancellation ‘
[normal]due to unplanned runway closure
[normal]’
[normal] – and asking for feedback, although there was no link to give this.
[normal]We would like answers to the following points:
[normal]1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Why were there no senior airport staff in evidence in North terminal even though there must have been many senior people in the airport?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Wh
[normal]y were the toilets in North terminal not working when all the revenue earning shops, restaurants, and arcades were fine?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Why were we routed through South terminal and then a lengthy, confusing and convoluted route back to the North terminal we had left a
[normal] couple of hours earlier?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Why were we not told formally of the cancellation until we got home?
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Why did it take 3 hours to get our baggage back.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Unplanned runway closure as the reason for cancellation does not seem to stack up as Gatwick only has one run
[normal]way and there were numerous flights landing and taking off from South terminal.
